<br>
When I graduated from college, I chose to pursue a horrendously stressful job in which I made a lot of money (Investment banking, complete with 120+ hour work weeks, showers in the office, and sleeping under your desk if you were lucky, not sleeping at all if you were unlucky).  Basically, I decided it would be better to work my ass off for a short time and be miserable but finish up early and have enough money so I was financially independent.  This is one school of thought.  The other is to find a lower paying job that you actually enjoy and can do throughout most of your life.  Only you can decide what is best for you.<br>
<br>
However, if it's not the nature of the job/profession itself, and rather is just because the person you work for is particularly unpleasant, then you just need to find a comparable position in another company.<br>
<br>
I'm sure you know that no drugs/alcohol will make the problem better and are just blowing off some steam.<br>
<br>
While drugs in your coffee will not solve the problem, perhaps drugs in your boss's coffee could substantially improve your working environment.<br>
<br>
